social_posts.post_text: Just when we got out of the weeds, we got pulled back in😫. Both of my babies are feeling bad. Tonight will be filled with boogie wipes, bone broth, epsom salt baths and a lot of hugs. | Dear New dad, a big key to dealing with your child or children not feeling good, is to mentally prepare yourself for something you have no control over. It sucks to have to watch them go through the coughing, congestion, sleepless night etc. Being in a place/mindset of frustration makes it worst. Intentionally and strategically plan your days and nights out so that things get done sooner than later, create calming spaces, don’t try to take on task that you don’t need to take on while tending to your kid(s). Try to avoid giving them products that claim to replenish electrolytes, only to fill their body with a bunch of sugars and artificial flavoring. Keep them hydrated. Let them rest. Hope this helps. Maybe these will help too👉🏾 #helloharperskye #kendallraej

Here are some interesting scientific facts about our smiles, and why becoming a person that smiles often can change your life.

Simulating a genuine smile can boost your mood: Psychologists have found that even if you’re in bad mood, you can instantly lift your spirits by simulating (not fake, but choose to engage in)  a genuine smile.
.
It boosts your immune system: Smiling really can improve your physical health, too. Your body is more relaxed when you smile, which contributes to good health and a stronger immune system.
.
Smiles are contagious: It’s not just a saying: smiling really is contagious, scientists say. In a study conducted in Sweden, people had difficulty frowning when they looked at other subjects who were smiling, and their muscles twitched into smiles all on their own.
.
Smiles Relieve Stress: Your body immediately releases endorphins when you smile, even when you force it. This sudden change in mood will help you feel better and -release stress.
.
Smiles use from 5 to 53 facial muscles: Just smiling can require your body to use up to 53 muscles, but some smiles only use 5 muscle movements.
.
Women smile more than men: Generally, women smile more than men, but when they participate in similar work or social roles, they smile the same amount. This finding leads scientists to believe that gender roles are quite flexible. Boy babies, though, do smile lessthan girl babies, who also make more eye contact.
.
Smiles are more attractive than makeup: A research study conducted by Orbit Complete discovered that 69% of people find women more attractive when they smile than when they are wearing makeup.
.
There are 19 different types of smiles: UC-San Francisco researcher identified 19 types of smiles and put them into two categories: polite “social” smiles which engage fewer muscles, and sincere “felt” smiles that use more muscles on both sides of the face.

Dear new Dad, 
Sometimes you may need to sleep beside your son or daughters bed to help make them feel safe from the “boogie man,” or just so they can get used to their room. Sometimes it’s a good idea to just sit in their room and listen to their breathing pattern; just in case when they’re not sleeping right, you can spot the different patterns. I say sleep, “fake sleep,” or sit somewhere in the room versus in their bed because it makes it easier for you to leave the room without waking them up.
.
Our Harper has been in a phase where she hasn’t been to fond of sleeping in her room alone lately. She says “Dad my room is ugly,” b.k.a there’s a boogie man. I’ve reassured her that Dad nor Mom wouldn’t let anything ever get her, and that there is no ANYTHING in her bathroom or room but good spirits watching over her.
.
To ease her mind before bed, we’ll pray, tell a fun story, and or I’ll use her teddy bear to do flying karate kick love taps to her forehead lol. She’ll then proceed to ask that I hold her hand until she falls asleep.
.

Real Estate Game ** Do not put property in a minor’s name. They cannot convey title until age 18. So create a Trust and purchase it in the trust for the “benefit” of that child. Then have the child work the property so they learn. Pay them to work it. Make the profits go partly to a college 529 savings plan for your kid and the rest to a custodial 401k in their name to give them a retirement plan now. They can borrow against the 401k for future properties. 💯

If you’ve ever seen my post about me sleeping near my daughters bed, in the chair or on the floor to listen to their breathing patterns, it’s because I want/wanted to be aware of their sleeping habits. This post is a p.s.a to make you aware that the constant congestion you may be hearing may not be a cold, flu and or virus at all. It may be something out of your control. I know it sucks. Hang in there. Do your due diligence to be aware of the changes in your child’s behavior or breathing etc. Also be mindful of your child’s reaction to foods. A lot kids react and build mucus after eating dairy in any shape or form. The air quality in your house can play a roll in certain repetitive sicknesses as well. It can be helpful to get your duct work cleaned and stay on top of your filter changing. New Dad…YOU GOT THIS👊🏾

Have you ever heard exactly what you needed to hear in the most divine moment of your life? Well up until now, all of my business endeavors have been funded from our own pockets. 3 businesses, multiple properties, all funded by us. I have been allergic to borrowing money ever since I got myself out of debt in my 20’s. So last night after a long day of filming, interviewing new real estate agents and deliberating on how we would quickly scale Indigo Road, I was debating on whether we should seek other sources of funding to reach our goals faster. Honestly, just that thought made me feel itchy and I got hives. So we left work and went to see @tylerperry in his documentary #MaxinesBaby and OMG!!! If God wasn’t talking straight to me. Tyler revealed that he had always funded his projects and kept full control and ownership. He never liked giving up any creative control or accepting money. Then he realized in order to accomplish his dream of Tyler Perry Studios, it finally made sense to accept additional sources in order to reach his legacy. That sat with me all night. OWNERSHIP is always the goal. However as an entrepreneur stretching myself, his decisions and assurance were the perfect advice and resolve to hear. 🙏🏽🙏🏽 GOD always gives us the answers if we listen.
